# Allowlist for `claude` CLI invocations inside synced shell scripts.
# See .claude/lint-claude-cli-invocations.py — the lint hashes each
# `# claude-cli-invocations:start` / `:end` region and refuses to pass
# if the (hash, path) pair isn't listed here. Adding or rotating an
# entry requires byte-level review of the locked region in the same PR.
#
# Format (whitespace-separated): <sha256>  <path>  <description>
#
# The path field binds each approval to a specific source file —
# copying an allowlisted region into a new synced .sh file does NOT
# inherit the approval; the reviewer has to add a separate entry.

53d15c3ae0db8e302b3290ab7d08c8172aff9199f68da710f09296f8674cf08e  .claude/skills/agent-loop/scripts/agent-loop.sh  agent-loop.sh: spawn claude with bypassPermissions + consumer-owned prompt (with {ISSUE_ID} placeholder guard)
